All-purpose?

815
00:31:50,125 --> 00:31:52,736
Cameras, all sizes.

816
00:31:52,780 --> 00:31:55,000
A lineman's telephone
that you hook up

817
00:31:55,043 --> 00:31:57,132
anywhere you have access
to the wires.

818
00:31:57,176 --> 00:31:59,047
Oh, wow.

819
00:31:59,091 --> 00:32:02,398
All kinds of wireless
video and audio monitoring.

820
00:32:02,442 --> 00:32:04,357
Hidden microphones.

821
00:32:05,532 --> 00:32:07,447
Badges, I.D. Cards...

822
00:32:07,490 --> 00:32:09,753
A peephole lens
for your camcorder.

823
00:32:09,797 --> 00:32:10,754
Really?

824
00:32:10,798 --> 00:32:12,452
Drill a hole in the wall

825
00:32:12,495 --> 00:32:14,236
attach this to your camcorder

826
00:32:14,280 --> 00:32:16,630
and you get the big picture
in the next room.

827
00:32:20,025 --> 00:32:21,200
Oh.

828
00:32:22,592 --> 00:32:27,293
Recorder, wall probes--
lets you hear through walls.

829
00:32:27,336 --> 00:32:30,122
An electronic tracking device.

830
00:32:30,165 --> 00:32:32,907
You attach this to the car
you want to follow

831
00:32:32,951 --> 00:32:34,865
and then this piece,
the receiver

832
00:32:34,909 --> 00:32:37,042
lets you hear
a continuous beep, beep, beep

833
00:32:37,085 --> 00:32:37,999
in your own car.

834
00:32:38,043 --> 00:32:39,044
[ Beeping]

835
00:32:39,087 --> 00:32:41,046
Perfect.

836
00:32:41,089 --> 00:32:42,699
Do you have a catalog?

837
00:32:49,315 --> 00:32:51,099
Oh, wow!

838
00:32:52,100 --> 00:32:53,232
Woman:
Ginny got caught.

839
00:32:53,275 --> 00:32:55,016
Man:
Then why aren't you home
with her?

840
00:32:55,060 --> 00:32:56,148
Woman:
Why aren't you?

841
00:32:56,191 --> 00:32:57,149
Who's the mom?

842
00:32:57,192 --> 00:32:58,498
It's your kid too!

843
00:32:58,541 --> 00:32:59,499
Don't push me.

844
00:32:59,542 --> 00:33:00,935
Police officer.

845
00:33:00,979 --> 00:33:01,892
Hey, hey!

846
00:33:01,936 --> 00:33:03,111
Hey!

847
00:33:03,155 --> 00:33:05,287
Woman:
What're you doing, man?

848
00:33:05,331 --> 00:33:07,246
Get the hell off of him,
will you?

849
00:33:07,289 --> 00:33:08,203
Go home.

850
00:33:08,247 --> 00:33:09,683
Listen,
leave him alone!

851
00:33:09,726 --> 00:33:10,684
Stand back!

852
00:33:10,727 --> 00:33:11,685
He's my husband!

853
00:33:11,728 --> 00:33:12,642
Leave my wife alone!

854
00:33:12,686 --> 00:33:14,122
Get off him!

855
00:33:14,166 --> 00:33:16,037
Don't cuff him!

856
00:33:16,081 --> 00:33:16,995
Listen!

857
00:33:17,038 --> 00:33:17,996
Matthew, take him!

858
00:33:18,039 --> 00:33:19,040
It's our runaway.

859
00:33:19,084 --> 00:33:20,911
You guys...

860
00:33:20,955 --> 00:33:23,827
Woman:
I am trying to tell you!

861
00:33:23,871 --> 00:33:25,307
Tara!

862
00:33:25,351 --> 00:33:26,700
Tara!

863
00:33:26,743 --> 00:33:28,702
Tara!

864
00:33:28,745 --> 00:33:32,010
[ Classical music playing]

865
00:33:35,361 --> 00:33:37,102
[ Laughing]

866
00:33:37,145 --> 00:33:38,146
Okay.

867
00:33:38,190 --> 00:33:39,321
Bye.

868
00:33:45,806 --> 00:33:48,417
[ No audio]

869
00:33:48,461 --> 00:33:49,984
[ Softly]:
Say that again?

870
00:33:50,028 --> 00:33:51,159
[ No audio]

871
00:33:51,203 --> 00:33:52,421
Yes, that's it.

872
00:33:52,465 --> 00:33:53,901
Okay.

873
00:34:16,489 --> 00:34:18,534
[ Laughs]

874
00:34:20,623 --> 00:34:23,322
It's like an o'keeffe
still life, isn't it?

875
00:34:25,367 --> 00:34:27,500
You know
what Alfred stieglitz said

876
00:34:27,543 --> 00:34:31,112
when he saw Georgia o'keeffe's
art work for the first time?

877
00:34:31,156 --> 00:34:34,898
He said,
"finally, a woman on paper."

878
00:34:34,942 --> 00:34:36,291
I didn't know that.

879
00:34:36,335 --> 00:34:38,032
Yeah, he said that.

880
00:34:39,729 --> 00:34:41,166
Wonderful party.

881
00:34:45,257 --> 00:34:46,171
Tara.

882
00:34:46,214 --> 00:34:47,215
Aw, honey.

883
00:34:47,259 --> 00:34:50,175
Honey, I was so worried
about you.

884
00:34:50,218 --> 00:34:53,700
Nice to see Mrs. Delaney
with a happy ending, huh?

885
00:34:53,743 --> 00:34:54,962
Yeah, for a change.

886
00:34:55,005 --> 00:34:56,137
I missed you.

887
00:34:56,181 --> 00:34:57,921
I missed you, too.

888
00:34:57,965 --> 00:34:59,140
Woman:
Shirley, line two.

889
00:34:59,184 --> 00:35:00,272
Usually these...

890
00:35:01,882 --> 00:35:02,709
[ Sniffling]

891
00:35:02,752 --> 00:35:04,232
I want to go home.

892
00:35:05,712 --> 00:35:07,496
It's a nice change.

893
00:35:15,722 --> 00:35:17,027
You are here alone.

894
00:35:19,204 --> 00:35:20,466
Me, too.

895
00:35:21,597 --> 00:35:23,643
Would you like to dance?

896
00:35:23,686 --> 00:35:24,687
Here?

897
00:35:24,731 --> 00:35:25,949
Yeah.

898
00:35:25,993 --> 00:35:28,474
Or anywhere you like.

899
00:35:28,517 --> 00:35:33,218
Um, actually, someone's
coming to pick me up.

900
00:35:33,261 --> 00:35:34,741
Oh, lucky guy.

901
00:35:34,784 --> 00:35:35,916
Well...

902
00:35:38,571 --> 00:35:40,442
It would be my pleasure.

903
00:35:49,103 --> 00:35:51,758
In actuality,
it was like the pinkest sand

904
00:35:51,801 --> 00:35:53,412
I've ever seen in my life.

905
00:35:53,455 --> 00:35:55,370
Oh, excuse me.

906
00:35:55,414 --> 00:35:57,851
We should probably get together
in the morning.

907
00:35:57,894 --> 00:35:59,331
Okay, why?

908
00:35:59,374 --> 00:36:01,637
I think you're right to have
your suspicions.

909
00:36:01,681 --> 00:36:03,378
Did you see him
with someone?

910
00:36:03,422 --> 00:36:07,121
I had a little chat
with him myself, so to speak.

911
00:36:07,165 --> 00:36:09,210
I taped it, it's on tape.

912
00:36:09,254 --> 00:36:10,429
What's on tape?

913
00:36:12,474 --> 00:36:14,172
Did he make a pass at you?

914
00:36:15,825 --> 00:36:16,913
Oh, my god.

915
00:36:16,957 --> 00:36:18,176
Listen, we need more

916
00:36:18,219 --> 00:36:20,221
so don't breathe a word to him

917
00:36:20,265 --> 00:36:23,050
until we can come up
with some kind of a strategy.

918
00:36:23,093 --> 00:36:24,443
All right?

919
00:36:24,486 --> 00:36:25,922
Yeah, all right.

920
00:36:25,966 --> 00:36:27,663
Sally?

921
00:36:27,707 --> 00:36:28,925
Yeah, right.

922
00:36:34,322 --> 00:36:35,758
Craig:
What, babe?

923
00:36:37,978 --> 00:36:42,548
I'm just feeling thankful
that I have you to come home to.

924
00:36:49,946 --> 00:36:52,340
Well, now you know
how I felt all these years.

925
00:36:58,825 --> 00:37:00,435
We're so lucky.

926
00:37:20,586 --> 00:37:22,196
Gone? What do
you mean, gone?

927
00:37:22,240 --> 00:37:23,197
All his things.

928
00:37:23,241 --> 00:37:25,417
Yes. Gone.

929
00:37:25,460 --> 00:37:27,854
He took everything
he could get his hands on.

930
00:37:27,897 --> 00:37:29,159
Wait...

931
00:37:29,203 --> 00:37:31,205
Thank god
I still have my business.

932
00:37:31,249 --> 00:37:32,032
I don't under...

933
00:37:32,075 --> 00:37:33,163
I confronted him.

934
00:37:33,207 --> 00:37:34,339
I had to.

935
00:37:34,382 --> 00:37:37,864
Oh, Sally, I told you not to.

936
00:37:37,907 --> 00:37:38,952
I couldn't help it.

937
00:37:38,995 --> 00:37:40,170
What do you think?

938
00:37:40,214 --> 00:37:42,042
I mean, this has been
horrible for me.

939
00:37:42,085 --> 00:37:43,739
Okay.

940
00:37:44,827 --> 00:37:47,177
I'm sorry, Tess, I'm sorry.

941
00:37:47,221 --> 00:37:48,178
It's okay, it's okay.

942
00:37:48,222 --> 00:37:49,658
[ Sobbing]

943
00:37:49,702 --> 00:37:51,921
Hey, babe, don't beat
yourself up over it.

944
00:37:51,965 --> 00:37:53,140
It's not your fault.

945
00:37:53,183 --> 00:37:54,533
Yeah, it was.

946
00:37:54,576 --> 00:37:56,665
I shouldn't have said
anything to her

947
00:37:56,709 --> 00:37:59,320
till I had the guy
absolutely dead to rights.

948
00:37:59,364 --> 00:38:02,323
Most situations like this
require a professional.

949
00:38:02,367 --> 00:38:04,891
You know, your pipes break,
you call a plumber.

950
00:38:04,934 --> 00:38:07,110
What?

951
00:38:07,154 --> 00:38:08,938
Look, you were fine
before all this

952
00:38:08,982 --> 00:38:10,723
and if you quit
you'll be fine after.

953
00:38:10,766 --> 00:38:12,202
No, I'm not quitting.

954
00:38:12,246 --> 00:38:13,856
I'm not.

955
00:38:13,900 --> 00:38:17,295
Actually, Peter Fisher says
I can rent office space

956
00:38:17,338 --> 00:38:18,426
down at his firm.

957
00:38:18,470 --> 00:38:20,733
Do you think maybe
you're getting

958
00:38:20,776 --> 00:38:23,083
a little bit ahead
of yourself here?

959
00:38:23,126 --> 00:38:24,693
Office space, come on.

960
00:38:24,737 --> 00:38:27,130
Craig, when I see what happens
to these people

961
00:38:27,174 --> 00:38:28,871
my own sister...

962
00:38:28,915 --> 00:38:32,353
I... I want to do something.

963
00:38:32,397 --> 00:38:34,007
Honey, look, it is one thing

964
00:38:34,050 --> 00:38:35,748
to look up records
in a courthouse

965
00:38:35,791 --> 00:38:37,445
but you could get hurt.

966
00:38:37,489 --> 00:38:40,230
I'm not just talking
about your feelings.

967
00:38:40,274 --> 00:38:41,231
I'm very careful.

968
00:38:41,275 --> 00:38:42,842
No, these people, these...

969
00:38:42,885 --> 00:38:44,757
Some wacko you're trailing
finds out

970
00:38:44,800 --> 00:38:46,280
then youbecome the target.

971
00:38:46,324 --> 00:38:47,629
Oh...

972
00:38:47,673 --> 00:38:49,631
You walk into some
domestic altercation

973
00:38:49,675 --> 00:38:51,764
do you know that's how
more cops are killed?

974
00:38:51,807 --> 00:38:52,982
You never know

975
00:38:53,026 --> 00:38:54,854
what you're going
to walk into.

976
00:38:54,897 --> 00:38:59,554
Craig, for the first
time in my life there's...

977
00:38:59,598 --> 00:39:02,949
I found something that matters

978
00:39:02,992 --> 00:39:06,866
that... I can actually do.

979
00:39:06,909 --> 00:39:09,172
And I'm going to do it.

980
00:39:15,222 --> 00:39:17,398
Tess:
Yes, if you could just give US

981
00:39:17,442 --> 00:39:19,487
the correct spelling
of your name?

982
00:39:20,619 --> 00:39:21,881
Right... yes.

983
00:39:21,924 --> 00:39:24,710
That's how we have it
in our directory.

984
00:39:24,753 --> 00:39:27,408
Great.

985
00:39:27,452 --> 00:39:29,367
Thank you very much.

986
00:39:29,410 --> 00:39:30,411
Hello!

987
00:39:30,455 --> 00:39:31,412
How are you?

988
00:39:31,456 --> 00:39:32,457
I'm fine.

989
00:39:32,500 --> 00:39:33,936
Peter Fisher just told me

990
00:39:33,980 --> 00:39:35,721
you opened
your own office here.

991
00:39:35,764 --> 00:39:36,722
Yeah. Come on in.

992
00:39:36,765 --> 00:39:38,158
It's nice to see you again.

993
00:39:38,201 --> 00:39:39,159
You, too.

994
00:39:39,202 --> 00:39:40,595
I wanted you to know

995
00:39:40,639 --> 00:39:42,597
that Maggie and I
are in counseling.

996
00:39:42,641 --> 00:39:43,598
We're trying

997
00:39:43,642 --> 00:39:44,947
to make it work out.

998
00:39:44,991 --> 00:39:45,948
Good.

999
00:39:45,992 --> 00:39:47,602
That's wonderful.

1000
00:39:47,646 --> 00:39:48,516
Um, do you want to...

1001
00:39:48,560 --> 00:39:50,083
No, I'm not
going to keep you.

1002
00:39:50,126 --> 00:39:52,564
I just came by to say thanks
for everything

1003
00:39:52,607 --> 00:39:54,348
and I wish you
the best of luck.

1004
00:39:59,440 --> 00:40:00,180
You take care.

1005
00:40:00,223 --> 00:40:02,269
Okay.

1006
00:40:05,490 --> 00:40:06,447
Hey!

1007
00:40:06,491 --> 00:40:07,796
Hey!

1008
00:40:09,494 --> 00:40:10,451
Who's that?

1009
00:40:10,495 --> 00:40:11,452
Who's that guy?

1010
00:40:11,496 --> 00:40:13,759
Oh, a client.

1011
00:40:13,802 --> 00:40:15,064
Oh, guess what?

1012
00:40:15,108 --> 00:40:16,849
Another firm's put me
on retainer.

1013
00:40:16,892 --> 00:40:19,112
Oh, boy, terrific.

1014
00:40:22,898 --> 00:40:25,771
Yes, Mr. Turner, Tess McCall.

1015
00:40:25,814 --> 00:40:26,859
Yeah, I spoke to him.

1016
00:40:26,902 --> 00:40:28,208
I got his particulars

1017
00:40:28,251 --> 00:40:31,211
and I think it's a good place
to start.

1018
00:40:31,254 --> 00:40:32,430
Yeah.

1019
00:40:32,473 --> 00:40:34,301
Why don't...

1020
00:40:34,344 --> 00:40:35,737
Well, we'll have a meeting
tomorrow morning, 9:00.

1021
00:40:35,781 --> 00:40:37,957
Okay, great, thanks.

1022
00:40:38,000 --> 00:40:38,914
Geez, honey...

1023
00:40:38,958 --> 00:40:40,786
So who, uh,
who was that guy?

1024
00:40:40,829 --> 00:40:42,527
Oh, I told you,
he was a client.

1025
00:40:42,570 --> 00:40:43,789
Yeah?

1026
00:40:45,355 --> 00:40:46,313
What?

1027
00:40:46,356 --> 00:40:47,662
I saw the guy hugging you.

1028
00:40:47,706 --> 00:40:49,142
I was just, you know...

1029
00:40:49,185 --> 00:40:50,099
A little jealous.

1030
00:40:50,143 --> 00:40:54,843
You are, aren't you?

1031
00:40:54,887 --> 00:40:57,019
Are you ready
to call it a day?

1032
00:40:57,063 --> 00:40:58,020
Let's go.

1033
00:40:58,064 --> 00:40:58,978
No, sweetie

1034
00:40:59,021 --> 00:41:00,719
I have three hours
of work left.

1035
00:41:00,762 --> 00:41:02,503
I can't, sorry.
Don't worry.

1036
00:41:02,547 --> 00:41:04,418
Dinner's in the slow cooker.

1037
00:41:06,420 --> 00:41:07,421
Okay.

1038
00:41:07,465 --> 00:41:08,422
Okay?

1039
00:41:08,466 --> 00:41:09,423
Yeah. All right.

1040
00:41:09,467 --> 00:41:10,424
I just...

1041
00:41:10,468 --> 00:41:11,251
See you later.

1042
00:41:11,294 --> 00:41:12,252
Okay.

1043
00:41:12,295 --> 00:41:13,427
Okay.

1044
00:41:21,870 --> 00:41:24,525
Man:
Hey, Ruth!

1045
00:41:24,569 --> 00:41:26,440
Ruth's out sick,
down with something.

1046
00:41:26,484 --> 00:41:27,789
Oh, yeah?

1047
00:41:27,833 --> 00:41:30,488
Who are you?

1048
00:41:30,531 --> 00:41:31,706
Noreen.

1049
00:41:31,750 --> 00:41:33,273
I'm filling in.

1050
00:41:44,023 --> 00:41:46,242
Don't waste your time
going in there.

1051
00:41:46,286 --> 00:41:47,983
The guy took out a lease

1052
00:41:48,027 --> 00:41:51,639
but he wasn't there two weeks.

1053
00:41:51,683 --> 00:41:53,075
I'll be up on nine

1054
00:41:53,119 --> 00:41:56,383
if you get lonesome
on your break.

1055
00:41:56,426 --> 00:41:58,124
I got a thermos.

1056
00:42:37,032 --> 00:42:38,381
[ Sighs]

1057
00:42:41,167 --> 00:42:42,124
[ Door opens]

1058
00:42:42,168 --> 00:42:43,169
[ Knocking]

1059
00:42:43,212 --> 00:42:44,605
Hey, you're back.

1060
00:42:44,649 --> 00:42:46,128
How was Florida?

1061
00:42:46,172 --> 00:42:48,522
Oh, you know how uncle frank
and aunt ida are.

1062
00:42:48,566 --> 00:42:50,480
Can't put your feet up
on anything.

1063
00:42:50,524 --> 00:42:51,525
Great look.

1064
00:42:51,569 --> 00:42:54,006
I leave town
and you blossom.

1065
00:42:54,049 --> 00:42:54,920
You doing okay?

1066
00:42:54,963 --> 00:42:56,530
So tell me,
how's it going?

1067
00:42:56,574 --> 00:42:58,619
Are you having the most
incredible time?

1068
00:42:58,663 --> 00:43:00,273
Yeah...

1069
00:43:00,316 --> 00:43:02,275
Yeah, I am.

1070
00:43:02,318 --> 00:43:04,277
I lose a husband

1071
00:43:04,320 --> 00:43:07,280
and you gain a career,
and a wardrobe.

1072
00:43:07,323 --> 00:43:09,761
Oh, neesie,
you were lucky.

1073
00:43:09,804 --> 00:43:10,805
You just don't know.

1074
00:43:10,849 --> 00:43:12,502
I know,
as devastating as it was

1075
00:43:12,546 --> 00:43:14,026
it could have been worse.

1076
00:43:14,069 --> 00:43:15,375
Some of these
men and women

1077
00:43:15,418 --> 00:43:17,159
are left practically
destitute

1078
00:43:17,203 --> 00:43:19,988
with no one to show them
how to protect themselves.

1079
00:43:20,032 --> 00:43:21,642
Maybe you ought to
teach a class.

1080
00:43:21,686 --> 00:43:22,687
[ Chuckles]

1081
00:43:22,730 --> 00:43:24,123
Maybe I ought to.

1082
00:43:25,994 --> 00:43:27,692
You know what you look like?

1083
00:43:27,735 --> 00:43:29,432
One of the lunchroom ladies

1084
00:43:29,476 --> 00:43:31,434
from when we were
in junior high.

1085
00:43:31,478 --> 00:43:32,566
[ Laughing]

1086
00:43:32,610 --> 00:43:33,611
You look good.

1087
00:43:33,654 --> 00:43:35,525
I mean, different.
Good different.

1088
