[ TV barely audible]

1354
00:57:06,945 --> 00:57:08,163
...scores!

1355
00:57:08,207 --> 00:57:09,513
[ Crowd cheering]

1356
00:57:09,556 --> 00:57:10,818
[ Rewinds tape]

1357
00:57:10,862 --> 00:57:12,385
Matthew:
I want 50 bucks now.

1358
00:57:12,429 --> 00:57:14,082
Yeah, I did, I did, I saw it.

1359
00:57:14,126 --> 00:57:16,998
I've been playing the same
game as the last...

1360
00:57:17,042 --> 00:57:19,044
[ Clicks off]

1361
00:57:20,567 --> 00:57:23,657
Announcer:
71-69.

1362
00:57:23,701 --> 00:57:25,703
[ Sighs]

1363
00:57:25,746 --> 00:57:28,706
[ Whistle blowing]

1364
00:57:49,161 --> 00:57:50,902
Boy:
Daddy, daddy!

1365
00:57:50,945 --> 00:57:52,773
[ Laughing]

1366
00:57:52,817 --> 00:57:54,166
Hi, sweetheart.

1367
00:57:54,209 --> 00:57:56,081
Have a nice day?

1368
00:57:56,124 --> 00:57:59,432
The dry cleaner called.

1369
00:57:59,476 --> 00:58:01,478
They won't have your suit
till tomorrow--

1370
00:58:01,521 --> 00:58:02,435
is that okay?

1371
00:58:02,479 --> 00:58:04,393
Boy:
Come on, dad.

1372
00:58:06,395 --> 00:58:08,397
Wife:
Here we go.

1373
00:58:12,271 --> 00:58:13,577
Boy:
Thanks.

1374
00:58:14,665 --> 00:58:16,536
I want to push
the button.

1375
00:58:17,581 --> 00:58:19,626
Uh, yes... uh
Benjamin Randall, please.

1376
00:58:19,670 --> 00:58:21,410
You'll have
to give them a moment.

1377
00:58:21,454 --> 00:58:23,630
Mrs. Randall and their kids
just went up.

1378
00:58:23,674 --> 00:58:24,718
[ Phone rings]

1379
00:58:24,762 --> 00:58:25,676
Door.

1380
00:58:25,719 --> 00:58:28,113
Mm-hmm.

1381
00:58:28,156 --> 00:58:30,942
Wife and kids?

1382
00:58:32,030 --> 00:58:34,119
Statements from two banks

1383
00:58:34,162 --> 00:58:36,991
where he opened accounts
with your money.

1384
00:58:37,035 --> 00:58:38,515
[ Laughing]

1385
00:58:38,558 --> 00:58:39,472
Oh, no.

1386
00:58:39,516 --> 00:58:43,302
[ Continues laughing]

1387
00:58:43,345 --> 00:58:44,825
A wife?

1388
00:58:47,045 --> 00:58:49,177
Do the kids look like him?

1389
00:58:51,266 --> 00:58:53,138
I suppose...

1390
00:58:53,181 --> 00:58:54,922
Yes.

1391
00:58:54,966 --> 00:58:56,402
[ Catching breath]

1392
00:58:59,536 --> 00:59:01,320
Sally, we should
go see your attorney.

1393
00:59:01,363 --> 00:59:02,669
We should do it right away.

1394
00:59:02,713 --> 00:59:04,628
Yeah.

1395
00:59:04,671 --> 00:59:07,500
[ Sobs]

1396
00:59:09,371 --> 00:59:11,635
Can we do this tomorrow,
please?

1397
00:59:13,245 --> 00:59:17,205
[ Crickets chirping]

1398
00:59:33,831 --> 00:59:36,007
[ Rewinds tape]

1399
00:59:36,050 --> 00:59:37,443
Woman:
Hi, it's Linda.

1400
00:59:37,486 --> 00:59:38,618
Craig:
Hey.

1401
00:59:38,662 --> 00:59:40,664
So, guess what
I did tonight?

1402
00:59:40,707 --> 00:59:41,665
What?

1403
00:59:41,708 --> 00:59:43,492
Sold my tenth car.

1404
00:59:43,536 --> 00:59:44,493
Really? Cool.

1405
00:59:44,537 --> 00:59:46,321
Was he good-looking?

1406
00:59:46,365 --> 00:59:47,496
Oh-ho! You're so bad.

1407
00:59:47,540 --> 00:59:49,716
You're going to pay
for that, you know.

1408
00:59:49,760 --> 00:59:50,717
Really?

1409
00:59:50,761 --> 00:59:51,631
Uh-huh.

1410
00:59:51,675 --> 00:59:53,546
Is that a problem?

1411
00:59:53,590 --> 00:59:56,201
[ Both laughing]

1412
00:59:56,244 --> 00:59:58,507
So, uh, we're still on
for tomorrow, right?

1413
00:59:58,551 --> 00:59:59,465
Yeah.

1414
00:59:59,508 --> 01:00:00,466
7:00?

1415
01:00:00,509 --> 01:00:01,467
Room 116.

1416
01:00:01,510 --> 01:00:02,337
Room 116.

1417
01:00:02,381 --> 01:00:04,644
[ Door opens]

1418
01:00:04,688 --> 01:00:06,646
[ Clicks machine off]

1419
01:00:15,699 --> 01:00:17,091
Hey, babe, you're back.

1420
01:00:17,135 --> 01:00:19,398
I finished early.

1421
01:00:20,573 --> 01:00:23,097
Hey...

1422
01:00:23,141 --> 01:00:24,664
Did you have a good trip?

1423
01:00:24,708 --> 01:00:26,057
Yeah.

1424
01:00:26,100 --> 01:00:27,232
I'm running late.

1425
01:00:27,275 --> 01:00:28,668
I got to pick up Matty.

1426
01:00:28,712 --> 01:00:31,497
Spence is being transferred
to the second precinct.

1427
01:00:31,540 --> 01:00:33,586
So we're throwing
a little party for him.

1428
01:00:33,630 --> 01:00:35,457
That's why I'm scarfing down
a hot dog.

1429
01:00:35,501 --> 01:00:37,242
You don't mind
if I go, do you?

1430
01:00:37,285 --> 01:00:38,243
No, of course not.

1431
01:00:38,286 --> 01:00:40,245
I'm going to bed early anyway.

1432
01:00:40,288 --> 01:00:42,203
So, did you get the bad guys?

1433
01:00:42,247 --> 01:00:44,205
Yeah.

1434
01:00:44,249 --> 01:00:45,816
Cool.

1435
01:00:47,861 --> 01:00:51,648
[ Quietly]:
You don't know it yet,
but, yeah.

1436
01:00:57,392 --> 01:00:59,351
[ Faucets squeaking]

1437
01:00:59,394 --> 01:01:02,354
[ Shower running]

1438
01:01:06,401 --> 01:01:10,188
[ Dog barking in distance]

1439
01:01:23,070 --> 01:01:26,334
[ Thunder rumbling]

1440
01:01:34,647 --> 01:01:44,004
[ Beeping]

1441
01:01:44,048 --> 01:01:47,921
Radio announcer: We're high atop the radio towers overlooking lake erie.

1442
01:01:47,965 --> 01:01:50,532
It's music into the night.

1443
01:01:54,798 --> 01:01:58,889
And here's one from 1975.

1444
01:01:58,932 --> 01:02:03,284
♪ My eyes adored you

1445
01:02:03,328 --> 01:02:05,852
♪ though I never
laid a hand on you ♪

1446
01:02:05,896 --> 01:02:10,030
♪ my eyes adored you

1447
01:02:10,074 --> 01:02:12,163
♪ like a million miles
away from me ♪

1448
01:02:12,206 --> 01:02:15,035
♪ you couldn't see
how I adored you ♪

1449
01:02:16,820 --> 01:02:18,691
♪ so close

1450
01:02:18,735 --> 01:02:24,523
♪ so close
and yet so far ♪

1451
01:02:24,566 --> 01:02:26,917
♪ carried your books
from school ♪

1452
01:02:26,960 --> 01:02:31,660
♪ playing make-believe
you're married to me ♪

1453
01:02:31,704 --> 01:02:33,053
♪ you were fifth grade

1454
01:02:33,097 --> 01:02:34,794
♪ I was sixth

1455
01:02:34,838 --> 01:02:37,666
♪ when we came to be...

1456
01:02:37,710 --> 01:02:40,757
The toilet in the guest room
is broken, did I tell you?

1457
01:02:40,800 --> 01:02:43,237
You have to jiggle it
every time you flush.

1458
01:02:44,761 --> 01:02:46,632
Want me to call them?

1459
01:02:48,895 --> 01:02:51,202
I'm just not quite sure
what to tell them.

1460
01:02:51,245 --> 01:02:53,117
Well, just what you told me.

1461
01:02:53,160 --> 01:02:54,771
You have to jiggle it.

1462
01:03:00,907 --> 01:03:02,517
What, you want me
to call them?

1463
01:03:02,561 --> 01:03:03,562
No, I will.

1464
01:03:03,605 --> 01:03:05,564
Well, if you want me to,
just say so.

1465
01:03:05,607 --> 01:03:06,739
No, I said I would.

1466
01:03:09,655 --> 01:03:11,788
Fine. Call.

1467
01:03:13,833 --> 01:03:15,704
Oh, whoa-whoa-- lunch.

1468
01:03:15,748 --> 01:03:16,923
Keep going.

1469
01:03:16,967 --> 01:03:17,794
You're going
to be late.

1470
01:03:17,837 --> 01:03:18,838
Bye, mom.

1471
01:03:18,882 --> 01:03:20,013
Bye, sweetie.

1472
01:03:20,057 --> 01:03:21,406
Bye, dad. See you
after school.

1473
01:03:21,449 --> 01:03:22,668
Bye.

1474
01:03:22,711 --> 01:03:24,278
Bye, sweetheart.
Have a good day.

1475
01:03:24,322 --> 01:03:25,584
I had some files.

1476
01:03:25,627 --> 01:03:26,846
Did you see them?

1477
01:03:26,890 --> 01:03:28,065
No.

1478
01:03:28,108 --> 01:03:29,066
You sure?

1479
01:03:29,109 --> 01:03:30,023
Of course.

1480
01:03:30,067 --> 01:03:31,982
Why would I see them?

1481
01:03:34,854 --> 01:03:38,075
'Cause sometimes
you see them.

1482
01:03:38,118 --> 01:03:40,729
Are you saying
I go through your things...?

1483
01:03:40,773 --> 01:03:41,992
'Cause I don't.

1484
01:03:42,035 --> 01:03:44,037
Yeah, you do.

1485
01:03:44,081 --> 01:03:45,822
Why would I...?

1486
01:03:48,563 --> 01:03:50,652
If I wanted to see
your stupid files

1487
01:03:50,696 --> 01:03:52,872
I could do it without
you even knowing it.

1488
01:03:52,916 --> 01:03:55,179
[ Chuckles]
Yeah, sure.

1489
01:03:55,222 --> 01:03:57,181
All right. I'll see you.

1490
01:04:00,880 --> 01:04:03,317
Tess:
Copies of bank statements...

1491
01:04:03,361 --> 01:04:06,103
Marriage certificates,
I.D.S...

1492
01:04:06,146 --> 01:04:08,322
And photos.

1493
01:04:08,366 --> 01:04:10,629
God, I can't believe
this was going on

1494
01:04:10,672 --> 01:04:12,805
and I was completely
blind to it!

1495
01:04:12,849 --> 01:04:14,024
Hell of a job, Tess.

1496
01:04:14,067 --> 01:04:16,461
You and I need
to get together sometime.

1497
01:04:16,504 --> 01:04:19,246
My friend could use an
investigator with your
kind of fortitude.

1498
01:04:19,290 --> 01:04:21,205
I'll call
the d.A.'S office.

1499
01:04:21,248 --> 01:04:22,380
Sally:
Thanks.

1500
01:04:26,079 --> 01:04:29,778
A hell of a job, Tess,
he's right.

1501
01:04:29,822 --> 01:04:31,302
Thank you.

1502
01:04:32,303 --> 01:04:34,174
[ Patting on back]

1503
01:04:44,010 --> 01:04:45,794
Hey, babe.

1504
01:04:51,670 --> 01:04:53,672
[ Softly]:
Hey... listen.

1505
01:04:58,633 --> 01:05:01,114
I'm sorry about this morning.

1506
01:05:01,158 --> 01:05:03,116
I am, I was a real jerk.

1507
01:05:05,423 --> 01:05:07,773
I'll call the plumber.

1508
01:05:07,816 --> 01:05:10,384
I'll take care
of everything, babe.

1509
01:05:10,428 --> 01:05:12,125
I'm so sorry.

1510
01:05:14,649 --> 01:05:15,781
Hey...

1511
01:05:18,436 --> 01:05:22,005
Remember when we used
to do this, huh?

1512
01:05:22,048 --> 01:05:23,920
I'd come home for lunch.

1513
01:05:31,144 --> 01:05:33,146
[ Whispers]:
Hey...

1514
01:05:35,018 --> 01:05:37,759
Why don't you let me
take this off?

1515
01:05:38,630 --> 01:05:39,718
Honey?

1516
01:05:47,639 --> 01:05:49,597
I...

1517
01:05:49,641 --> 01:05:51,599
I have to meet Denise.

1518
01:05:51,643 --> 01:05:53,732
What? Well...

1519
01:05:53,775 --> 01:05:56,561
Call her and tell her
you can't make it.

1520
01:05:57,431 --> 01:05:58,780
Hey...

1521
01:06:05,787 --> 01:06:07,833
[ Sighs]

1522
01:06:07,876 --> 01:06:10,879
Everything I tell women
to look for

1523
01:06:10,923 --> 01:06:12,620
it's now happening to me.

1524
01:06:12,664 --> 01:06:14,796
And I think
it's been going on

1525
01:06:14,840 --> 01:06:16,929
for a really
long time, neese.

1526
01:06:16,973 --> 01:06:19,018
I just didn't
want to see it.

1527
01:06:19,062 --> 01:06:25,024
Tess... I haven't ever
said anything, but...

1528
01:06:25,068 --> 01:06:29,028
Craig at Laurel's wedding.

1529
01:06:29,072 --> 01:06:33,032
I walked in on him
and Connie carpenter.

1530
01:06:33,076 --> 01:06:37,428
Her bridesmaid? So?

1531
01:06:37,471 --> 01:06:38,864
What do you mean?

1532
01:06:38,907 --> 01:06:41,823
In a bedroom.

1533
01:06:41,867 --> 01:06:44,435
You've known about this,
for...

1534
01:06:44,478 --> 01:06:45,827
Five years...!

1535
01:06:45,871 --> 01:06:47,873
And you've kept it
a secret?

1536
01:06:47,916 --> 01:06:49,875
I-I-I... kept it a secret?

1537
01:06:49,918 --> 01:06:51,224
I just didn't...

1538
01:06:51,268 --> 01:06:52,791
I couldn't tell you.

1539
01:06:52,834 --> 01:06:54,749
How dare you tell me now!

1540
01:06:54,793 --> 01:06:57,404
How dare you
even talk to me!

1541
01:06:57,448 --> 01:06:58,623
Tess!

1542
01:07:00,755 --> 01:07:02,583
[ Sighs]

1543
01:07:16,902 --> 01:07:21,907
Would you like me to fix you
something to eat before you go?

1544
01:07:21,950 --> 01:07:23,430
I'd be happy to.

1545
01:07:23,474 --> 01:07:25,128
I know you would,
mother.

1546
01:07:25,171 --> 01:07:28,305
I'll probably just
stop for something
on the way.

1547
01:07:35,529 --> 01:07:37,923
Anyway,
I'm sure Brett

1548
01:07:37,966 --> 01:07:40,186
will be
too mortified

1549
01:07:40,230 --> 01:07:42,797
to show his face
in here.

1550
01:07:47,193 --> 01:07:48,238
[ Sighs]

1551
01:07:48,281 --> 01:07:50,457
Mom...

1552
01:07:50,501 --> 01:07:52,459
What?

1553
01:07:53,330 --> 01:07:54,461
What?

1554
01:07:54,505 --> 01:07:56,768
[ Choked up]:
It's nothing.

1555
01:07:56,811 --> 01:07:58,117
I'm sorry.

1556
01:07:58,161 --> 01:08:00,119
Oh...
You always do this.

1557
01:08:00,163 --> 01:08:02,513
You always say,
"nothing."

1558
01:08:02,556 --> 01:08:03,644
No, I don't.

1559
01:08:03,688 --> 01:08:05,124
[ Chuckles]

1560
01:08:05,168 --> 01:08:07,735
Yes, you do, believe me.

1561
01:08:07,779 --> 01:08:11,913
You always deny stuff.

1562
01:08:11,957 --> 01:08:13,001
The obvious.

1563
01:08:13,045 --> 01:08:15,352
Yeah.

1564
01:08:15,395 --> 01:08:18,050
Oh, soph...

1565
01:08:18,094 --> 01:08:19,834
You get to be my age and...

1566
01:08:19,878 --> 01:08:23,708
And you think you're grown
and you have it all figured out

1567
01:08:23,751 --> 01:08:26,014
and I have so much
to figure out.

1568
01:08:26,058 --> 01:08:29,714
So is this, uh, a mid-life
thing or something?

1569
01:08:29,757 --> 01:08:31,585
Oh, god, I hope not yet.

1570
01:08:31,629 --> 01:08:34,110
[ Both laugh]

1571
01:08:36,634 --> 01:08:40,072
I am so...

1572
01:08:40,116 --> 01:08:41,421
Proud of you.

1573
01:08:41,465 --> 01:08:42,596
Yeah...

1574
01:08:42,640 --> 01:08:45,295
Guess I'm pretty proud
of you, too...

1575
01:08:45,338 --> 01:08:46,513
Mommy.

1576
01:08:46,557 --> 01:08:48,602
I trust you, soph.

1577
01:08:48,646 --> 01:08:50,865
I hope you know that.

1578
01:08:50,909 --> 01:08:52,389
Yeah, I do.

1579
01:08:52,432 --> 01:08:53,999
I do, mommy.

1580
01:08:54,042 --> 01:08:57,089
Whatever you decide
to do, okay?

1581
01:08:57,133 --> 01:08:59,439
I may rant or rave, but...

1582
01:08:59,483 --> 01:09:02,181
I'll support you, all right?

1583
01:09:02,225 --> 01:09:03,835
Yeah, I know.

1584
01:09:03,878 --> 01:09:04,879
Okay.

1585
01:09:04,923 --> 01:09:06,359
[ Chuckles]

1586
01:09:15,673 --> 01:09:17,849
Tess [with French accent]:
Mrs. Delaney...

1587
01:09:17,892 --> 01:09:19,024
Please-- Linda.

1588
01:09:19,067 --> 01:09:20,808
It's so luxurious.

1589
01:09:20,852 --> 01:09:22,245
Sinfully.

1590
01:09:22,288 --> 01:09:24,769
So, are you from here?

1591
01:09:24,812 --> 01:09:26,858
No, I'm from back east.

1592
01:09:26,901 --> 01:09:28,251
Miss it?

1593
01:09:28,294 --> 01:09:30,383
Well, my daughter's
with me and that helps

1594
01:09:30,427 --> 01:09:32,124
and there's this guy
I'm seeing.

1595
01:09:32,168 --> 01:09:35,562
Ah... that must help, too.

1596
01:09:35,606 --> 01:09:38,826
Well, no man's ever treated me
as well as he treats me.

1597
01:09:38,870 --> 01:09:40,480
Then you are lucky.

1598
01:09:40,524 --> 01:09:43,483
Well, I'm not that lucky--
he's married.

1599
01:09:43,527 --> 01:09:44,702
Well...

1600
01:09:44,745 --> 01:09:46,094
You never know.

1601
01:09:46,138 --> 01:09:48,836
In this case
I'm afraid I do know.

1602
01:09:48,880 --> 01:09:50,403
Sorry.

1603
01:09:50,447 --> 01:09:53,580
Even if he wasn't married,
this guy...

1604
01:09:53,624 --> 01:09:56,627
I get the feeling that
I'm not the first.

1605
01:09:56,670 --> 01:09:59,238
Our relationship
is what it is.

1606
01:09:59,282 --> 01:10:01,284
As long as we're
in room 116

1607
01:10:01,327 --> 01:10:02,937
it's a relationship.

1608
01:10:02,981 --> 01:10:04,374
I'm sorry to go on.

1609
01:10:04,417 --> 01:10:06,637
You want to take this
for a test drive?

1610
01:10:10,554 --> 01:10:13,687
Woman:
Hiya, Tess, he's out
on call right now.

1611
01:10:13,731 --> 01:10:15,123
Uh... Tess?

1612
01:10:26,439 --> 01:10:28,180
Is he with you?

1613
01:10:28,224 --> 01:10:30,878
He's out
with captain popkin--

1614
01:10:30,922 --> 01:10:32,924
a robbery over in chaney.

1615
01:10:32,967 --> 01:10:34,447
Tess, what is it?

1616
01:10:34,491 --> 01:10:36,971
You tell me.

1617
01:10:38,799 --> 01:10:40,453
You don't know?

1618
01:10:41,802 --> 01:10:42,977
No, I don't.

1619
01:10:43,021 --> 01:10:44,588
